Package honeyroasted.jype.type

Class TypeDeclaration

java.lang.Object
honeyroasted.jype.type.TypeDeclaration
All Implemented Interfaces:
TypePsuedo, Type
public class TypeDeclaration extends Object implements TypePsuedo
This class represents a declared type. That is, the actual declaration of a class or interface. It contains information about the declaration's name, type parameters, and parents. Instantiations of objects are represented by TypeParameterized. Every TypeParameterized has a corresponding TypeDeclaration, but a TypeDeclaration may have infinite possible TypeParameterizeds.

    • pathTo

      public Optional<List<TypeDeclaration>> pathTo(TypeDeclaration parent)
      Returns the inheritance path of TypeDeclarations needed to reach the given parent type. For example, if this TypeDeclaration represents the type Integer, the inheritance path necessary to reach Object is:
      • Integer
      • Number
      • Object
      Parameters:
      parent - The parent TypeDeclaration to construct an inheritance path to
      Returns:
      An optional containing the inheritance path, or an empty optional if one could not be found

    • lock

      public void lock()
      Description copied from interface: Type
      Locks this Type, making it immutable. Note that this does not necessarily lock the child Types of compound types such as TypeAnd. Since Type hierarchies can contain circular references, it may be necessary to instantiate Types, build their values, and then lock them to maintain immutability.
      Specified by:
      lock in interface Type
